==English==
===Etymology===
Named after [[physician]] [[w:Henry Heimlich|Henry Heimlich]] who described the procedure in 1974.  [http://patrickinstitute.org/press_release.htm Edward A. Patrick MD PhD] asserts that he is the co-developer and was denied credit by Heimlich.
[[Category:English eponyms]]

===Proper noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[first aid]] procedure used to treat [[choke|choking]].  The [[patient]] is [[lift]]ed from behind, squeezing their [[diaphragm]] to [[expel]] air and thereby [[dislodge|dislodging]] an [[obstruction]] in the [[windpipe]].
[[Category:Medicine]]